授課教師




課程簡介
公司理財


授課大綱
    This class intends to provide students a further understanding of financial strategy in a company. The class contains the topics of corporate investment, corporate financing, dividend, and value creation. 
    Since this class focuses on the application of financial strategies, this class will not only be in the format of lecture. An intensive discussion is definitely required. To participate, students should routinely read related articles from newspapers, magazines, and others. In addition, cases and group projects are designed to familiarize students the application of financial strategies. 
    Students who take this class are expected to possess the knowledge of fundamental financial management, such as discounting and valuation, CAPM, basic capital budgeting, and financial instruments. 






